---
layout: post
title:  Checking pyvenv virtual environment is active
date:   2019-04-18
categories: ["Python"]
---

To check if I am in a python virtual environment for pyvenv.
Pyvenv is included in Python3.3+ [^pyvenv]. 


When a virtual environment is not active `sys.prefix` will equal `sys.base_prefix`.
When a virtual envrionment is active the `sys.prefix` will be different to `sys.base_prefix`.

[^pyvenv]: [https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html](https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html)

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1871549/determine-if-python-is-running-inside-virtualenv